Hello,

Remember the time you spent searching for a complex command in an internal knowledge base only to copy-paste it to the terminal? Or updating dozens of servers altogether? *Snippets* can easily streamline both tasks.

Snippet is a command you can save in Termius for quick access, and it has many ways to simplify your life:

🧑‍💻 Access your *saved commands* in the terminal using autocomplete or the Snippets section in a side panel. Either way, you can run a saved command much faster than copy-pasting it from an internal doc. And it also works with broadcasting in split view.

🔀 Run commands *on multiple hosts*. E.g., you can run sudo apt-get update && apt-get upgrade when you need to update an entire fleet of servers. Select a command from a Snippets screen and run it on selected hosts and groups. You'll see the status of each execution so you can jump into the session for troubleshooting.

*Pro tip:* Save targets to a snippet to run the command on selected hosts with one click.

🚀 Run a command *on connection start* : cd to a specific directory or activate a work environment once connected. Go to a Host and save your snippet as a startup command for this.

Start with adding commands and organize them into *snippet packages* for easier navigation. You can even generate snippets using *AI*. Describe the action and click the magic wand button to get the command that'll do it.

